A film on the class-action lawsuit was screened at the Durban International Film Festival. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - A landmark court ruling has approved R5-billion compensation for miners affected by silicosis and their families. The documentary 'Dying for Gold' looks at the lives of such miners. READ: Victory for miners as they own half of Arnot Colliery The documentary screened at the Durban International Film Festival on Saturday. eNCA reporter Mawande Kheswa spoke to one of the directors, Richard Pakleppa. Watch the full interview in the video above.